{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Water Rooster also known as 癸酉''' (mizu no totori, kisui no tori, kiyuu) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 10th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Jinshin|ja|壬申}} and followed by {{ill|Koushoku|ja|甲戌}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|酉}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|金}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）}}) (i.e. Metal generates Water).

