It is the 10th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Jinshin|ja|壬申|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Koushoku|ja|甲戌|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Rooster|ja|酉|1=Rooster (zodiac)|lt=Rooster (酉)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Metal|ja|金|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|五行思想#相生（そうじょう）|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) (i.e. Metal generates Water).

